Dana van Dreven (born 8 July 1974), also known as DJ Lady Dana, is a Dutch hardstyle and previously gabber DJ and producer.
She started playing gabber in 1993 and though it was never her intention to become a DJ, she did, and is now the most popular female DJ on the Dutch hard dance scene.

She suffered a hiatus starting in 2010, after a series of medical conditions: she was first diagnosed with burnout after a series of anxiety episodes.
After a year of recovery, she was discovered with a melanoma and had her lymph glands removed.
After two and a half years, she returned to the last Thunderdome festival, where she performed a set using mostly one arm.
